column9: On Dec 6,2022, Beijing Office of the Leading Group for the Prevention and Control of Coronavirus, and Office of the Joint Prevention and Control Coordination Mechanism for the Capital's Strict Management in Entering Beijing decided the new measures for the nucleic acid detection and examination. When entering kindergartens and primary and secondary schools, people must scan the health code and check the negative certificate of nucleic acid test within 48 hours.    See website: https://archive.vn/iobIm.
column12: On Dec 19,2022, the Information Office of the Beijing Municipal People's Government organized The 432nd press conference on the prevention and control of novel coronavirus pneumonia.Beijing has cancelled the restrictions on arrival rate and trans-regional mobility and cancelled the requirement of "three days and three inspections" for employees arriving in Beijing. The regular nucleic acid testing requirements for employees of imported non cold chain goods, bulk construction, housing agency, accommodation services, libraries, cultural museums, art galleries, tourist attractions, production workshops, etc. are also cancelled.But according to a 10-point guideline released on December 7 to improve epidemic prevention and contro,staff working in elderly care institutions, child welfare institutions, kindergartens, primary and secondary schools, inpatient departments of medical institutions, catering (dining), indoor fitness as well as Internet cafes, bars, chess and card rooms, KTV, sauna and other closed places must scan the code and check the 48 hour nucleic acid negative certificate.    See website: https://web.archive.org/web/20230122075354/https://baijiahao.baidu.com/s?id=1752651528560939360&wfr=spider&for=pc
column15: On January 7, The State Council released the tenth version of the novel coronavirus infection prevention and control plan. column24: On January 7, The State Council released the tenth version of the novel coronavirus infection prevention and control plan. People infected with the novel coronavirus will no longer be quarantined, and tiered treatment will be implemented. Close contacts will no longer be identified, high or low risk areas will no longer be defined, all risk areas will be removed, and normal prevention and control measures will be implemented at the county, city and district level.    See website:   http://web.archive.org/web/20230201081718/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/TrCn7VO4xpUgVM4B5j2lXQ
column27: On Dec 18,2022, the Information Office of the Beijing Municipal People's Government organized the Beijing COVID-19 prevention and control leading group to resume work and production to carry out the network news release of epidemic prevention and control. The travel agencies and online tourism enterprises will resume the business of group tourism in Beijing, cross provincial group tourism in and out of Beijing.    See website: https://web.archive.org/web/20230122052945/https://baijiahao.baidu.com/s?id=1751568025626054048&wfr=spider&for=pc
column32: On July 29, 2022, the Beijing Municipal Civil Affairs Bureau issued a document granting an additional one-time living allowance of 400 yuan to each person living on subsistence allowances and in extreme poverty. Uninsured unemployed migrant workers who cannot return to work due to the impact of the epidemic, have no source of income for three months in a row, have difficulties in living and cannot be covered by unemployment insurance policies, and are not included in the scope of subsistence allowances, upon their application, they will be granted a one-time temporary relief fund to help them tide over their difficulties.  See website: http://web.archive.org/web/20230201090255/http://www.beijing.gov.cn/zhengce/zhengcefagui/202209/t20220902_2807304.html
column43: On Dec 6,2022, Beijing Office of the Leading Group for the Prevention and Control of Coronavirus, and Office of the Joint Prevention and Control Coordination Mechanism for the Capital's Strict Management in Entering Beijing decided the new measures for the nucleic acid detection and examination. column45: On Nov 12,2022, the Information Office of the Beijing Municipal People's Government organized The 411nd press conference on the prevention and control of novel coronavirus pneumonia.The management measures for close contacts have been adjusted from "7-day intensive isolation + 3-day home health monitoring" to "5-day intensive isolation + 3-day home isolation". column9: On January 6, the Office of the Beijing Leading Group for the Prevention and Control of the novel Coronavirus issued a document, saying that teachers, students and staff do not need to provide nucleic acid certificates to enter school gates. When the epidemic is not widespread, the school may check the nucleic acid certificate of the outside staff when they enter the school and no longer check the nucleic acid certificate of the outside staff. Primary and secondary schools affected by the epidemic may conduct online teaching or temporarily close down for a short period of time, and normal teaching order should be restored in a timely manner after the epidemic is over. column29: In order to thoroughly implement the Party Central Committee and the State Council's decision-making arrangements, we now develop temporary measures for the movement of Chinese and foreign personnel after the new coronavirus infection category B B tube, to be implemented from January 8, 2023.  Temporary measures for the movement of Chinese and foreign personnel mainly relate to the management of incoming personnel, as follows.  The incoming personnel will be tested for nucleic acid 48 hours before the trip, and those with negative results can come to China without applying for a health code from our embassies and consulates abroad and filling the results into the customs health declaration card. If the result is positive, the person concerned should come back to China after the result has turned negative.  No longer implement full nucleic acid testing for incoming personnel, and those with normal health declaration and no abnormalities in routine quarantine at customs ports can be released into the social side.    https://archive.ph/LHuSQ

column27: It is recommended to avoid and reduce movement between high COVID-19 epidemic areas.    http://web.archive.org/web/20230206075218/https://www.sohu.com/a/628340832_100260304

column29: “Chinese authorities announced the lifting of several major Covid-related entry restrictions that take effect on January 8…China has dropped quarantine requirements for all international arrivals…government … facilitating visa applications for foreign nationals traveling to China for business, employment, study, family visits and reunions…Travelers heading into China now are only required to take a nucleic acid test 48 hours before departure. Those with negative results no longer have to apply for a green health code from Chinese embassies and consulates abroad before entering. They do however need to fill in the results in their customs health declaration forms. If they test positive, they will not be permitted to travel to China until their tests come back negative.” See CNN website, archived:  https://web.archive.org/web/20230108214809/https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/china-reopening-tourism-explainer-intl-hnk/index.html
